“When it comes to personal and reproductive issues, Canadians don’t like paternalistic laws that take away freedoms.”

Canada should be trying to make abortion more difficult to get, not easier.

David explains that the “abortion pill” RU486 kills a baby at full gestation. The baby has already developed beating heart. It is still inside its mother, who is now on to having seven abortions. Fifteen days or more have passed since her abortion, and the baby is fully formed.

Six weeks is long enough to develop a functioning central nervous system. The unborn child feels pain, as evidenced by the fact that it stops developing a body curl reflex at thirty days post fertilization, at half gestational age. In utero ultrasounds have captured the unborn from fourteen days, showing the development of arms, legs, fingers, beating heart.

Two out of every three unborn men and women are abortions victims. Unable to live outside of their mother’s love and the care of their family, they have their very lives terminated. How is this a pro-choice issue? Not only is the unborn a developed person, it is a member of our species. It is used for experimentation more than almost any other species on the planet.

We have a lot to learn from David, how many abortions have you helped prevent or stopped already?

Please share your story with David and me? How can we stop this horror?
